inn1.comm: full outside off and a neat push square of the wicket wide of point
full on middle and off, defended back down the pitch
pushed across outside off, 81mph, left alone
on leg stump but he gets away with it as Azam flicks it off his pads and Rashid makes a diving stop at short fine-leg
back outside off, full length, defended towards mid-off
good line, full on off stump, 78mph, carefully defended with bat and pad together...a steady opening over
starts down the leg side, a hint of swing, Azhar misses his flick
nicely bowled, adjusts his line to full outside off, draws Azhar forward and he plays a flat-foot drive and almost gets an edge
down the leg side again, but this time Azhar had moved quite away across his crease the umpire lets it go
tucked off the pads to square leg
fuller on middle and leg, nudged just to the right of mid-on
full outside leg, not quite the right line, deflects off the pad fine of the keeper but the slow outfield ensures it pulls up well before the boundary...in fact, a small edge too
outside off, driven firmly to mid-off's left
back of a length outside off, left alone
driven square off a thickish outside edge towards point
gets across outside off and whips a full delivery into midwicket
nice drive this time, gets well forward into a full ball and pierces the gap between cover and mid-off...enough power to overcome the outfield, too
drags the length back a touch, pushed to mid-off
back of a length outside off, punched from the back foot to the left of mid-off so he keeps the strike
nearly draws an edge, angled across outside off, Azhar plays at it and the ball goes on to beat him
left alone this time

oh dear, Topley's had a bit of a shocker there! The ball was punched back to him, nothing was happening, but he went to throw it back to the keeper and the ball got stuck in his hand and he ended up winging it into space on the leg side to give away a run. A little embarrassing
clipped wide of mid-on
full outside off, left alone
good delivery, full at off stump, finds the outside edge but it dies in front of second slip who makes a sharp save
width outside off and cut through the off side, slow outfield into play
worked off the pads through square leg
driven back to the bowler without much timing
almost a drag on as he goes for an expansive drive, the ball doesn't come on and a thick inside edge dribbles just wide of the stumps
defended off the stumps
back of a length, aims to flick it through the on side but just gets taken on the thigh pad
that's a strong drive, a stride forward and although he wasn't to the pitch he just strikes clean thorugh the line
not so full this time, dropped into the off side and his Azhar's has gone flying somehow...a collision between him and Topley as the bowler ran across to get to the ball
tucked into the leg side
flicked down to long leg
better delivery, full and straight, squirts off a thick outside edge into the point area
very full, on the popping crease, driven off the bottom of the bat towards mid-off...Azhar struggling a little
full outside off, left alone
works a straight delivery behind square on the leg side with a flick of his wrists
blimey! That's come out of nowhere. He takes a step down the pitch and then crunches a full delivery straight down the ground over long off
stays in his crease this time, works a full ball from outside off towards mid-on
short of a length outside off, defended into the covers
more strong wrist work, taking a delivery from quite wide outside off and placing to just wide of mid-on
angled down to third man
slower ball, full and wide outside off, can't get it through the off side
width again, this time he is able to cut it wide of third man although it's just a single
shorter delivery, Azhar plays it off the back foot, rides it down to third man again
full at off stump, defended square to point
that's a sweet straight drive, along the ground this time, very correct from Azam as he leans into a full delivery and sends it straight of mid-off
short of a length, gets inside the line and tucks it down to long leg
full at straight, flicked to square leg
a bouncer, loops off the surface, Azam ducks and the umpire calls wide much to the chagrin of Woakes
sweetly time with a bottom-handed flick as he whips it off the stumps to mid-on
a punchy drive off the back foot which finds cover
finds the gap this time, another neat drive as he drives on the up through the covers
can't take advantage of some width as he cracks this one straight at cover
full at middle, 80mph, defended back to Topley
opens the face and runs this down to third man
slips out as a full toss but it doesn't cost him as it is flicked straight to short fine-leg
slower ball, full outside off, presses forward and opens the face to third man
leans back on the drive, finds point
down the pitch and gets beaten as Topley pulls his length back, the ball climbs over the top edge
full outside off, pushed to the covers, and a scream of 'no'
shorter outside off, played from the back foot this time
shuffles across his stumps and flicks a length delivery from outside off to deep square
a bouncer outside off, Azhar sways out of the line, this time it's okay for the umpire
fuller again, slides off a thick outside edge to third man
breakthrough! And it's the short ball which works. Entices a hook from this time, he had to drag it from outside off, took mostly top edge and Rashid steadied himself under the catch at long leg
starts on leg stump, flicked into the deep on the on side
on off stump, a little short, he has plenty of time to place it off the back foot through the covers
touch fuller, hint of turn, played with an open face to point
beats him as he tries to cut away a delivery that skidded on and only just missed off stump
chips this over mid-on, he came down the track but wasn't to the pitch. Still went through with his shot, dragged it a little, but had legs to get over the infield
pushed to the covers
full outside off, pushed square to backwards point
driven firmly to cover...Root gets a blow on his knee
angled into the pads, flicked to long leg
skips across the crease, almost has his feet off the ground as he flicks this to the leg side
goes for the pull, takes the pad and loops towards Root at slip
comes forward, defends down by his feet, looked for a single but the ball was quickly closed down
short outside off, he steps back and cuts through the off side
this spins a decent amount, but quite slowly and Hafeez flicks to mid-on
tossed up much more, is actually a low full toss, driven to long-off
played down the ground again
pushed carefully into the off side
full at leg stump, swept strongly behind square
full outside off, driven with a closed face into the leg side wide of mid-on
short of a length at off stump, Woakes has mixed things up quite effectively so far, worked into the leg side
this full delivery is drilled over the off side, confident shot from Hafeez who didn't bother with much footwork
straighter delivery, aims to work to the on side and Woakes gets across
comes forward and defends, slides off the face to point
pushed square into the off side again, point is quickly onto it to prevent the single
uses his feet, nicely bowled with a touch more air, pushes to the off side
short this time, spins away outside off, cut to deep cover

just over mid-on! Hafeez wanting to attack Rashid again, goes for the lofted option, the bat twisted in his hands a touch, didn't quite get the elevation he wanted but just enough to beat the man on the edge of the circle
this one has the distance! Down the pitch again, swings it very high into the air and it has the distance to land over the rope at long-on although not by much
dragged down outside off, flat-batted to deep cover
full toss which dips down the leg side, tickled fine of short fine-leg
over the wicket, tossed up on the stumps, tucked to square leg
goes back in the crease and flicks the ball a little finer for one
tossed up on middle and off, comes forward and pushes back to the bowler, briefly in the air
flighted, outside off, driven through the covers
gets across his stumps and taps one more through mid-on
Hafeez scuttles out and clips to leg, sends it straight to midwicket
pushed through outside off, drops back and chops through point
into the stands this time! Hafeez slaps Rashid upside his head again, walloping a full delivery over wide long-on... Picked the googly, I think
drags it down a little, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up outside off, driven through the covers
pushed through on middle and leg, Azhar clips through midwicket
floated up on the stumps, Hafeez gets down low to sweep but picks out the fielder
on the stumps, dabbed into a gap at midwicket and they hustle one
length ball, spinning in, clips the inside edge and runs square
flighted around off stump, blocked back to the bowler's left
down the leg side, just a little tickle of bat on it and the ball runs fine
presses forward and pushes a driven through mid-on
there's a clatter of timber, Buttler makes a half-hearted appeal... The ball went into and out of his gloves on to the stumps but was Hafeez's back foot in? Yes, it was indeedy
tossed up and punched through the covers
flighted outside off, tapped towards mid-off along the ground

calamity! Hafeez has run out his captain...! Steered the ball straight to backward point and then called Azhar through, but he was never in the picture, he turns and stops as if to remonstrate, swipes the air with his bat. To be fair, he didn't respond to the initial call and was then up the creek
gets forward and drives wide of the bowler for one
spinning away outside off, dabbed through backward point
on the stumps, whipped to leg and Safraz races through for one more
pushed into another gap for a busy single
beats the bat outside off, Hafeez attempting to cut off the back foot
Sarfraz is up and motoring, smoothly powering a sweep through backward square leg - 100 up for Pakistan
on the stumps, turned into the leg side but midwicket seizes on it
pushes the ball back to the bowler
spinning away outside off, dabbed square
turned into a gap
pushed through outside off, Sarfraz drops back and plays a very late cut for a couple
tossed up on middle and leg, nudged into the off side
gives it some air outside off, driven into the covers - tighter over from Rashid
shout of "catch!" from Moeen as Hafeez chips into a gap on the leg side
superbly done from Sarfraz, gets lower than Flo Rida Ft. T-Pain and sweeps hard from outside off off stump through backward square leg
on the stumps, worked to leg
driven, uppish and is that a drop? Well, hard to call it a chance but Woakes, I think, got fingertips to it diving forward at extra cover
punched back down the track
tossed up and swept hard, bounces out towards deep midwicket
length ball outside off, dabbed towards backward point
tossed up and punched into the covers coming forwards
tossed up and punched into the covers
nicely bowled, flighted on off stump and turning to beat Hafeez's forward prod
gets into line and dabs it away - another dot for Rashid
and that's a rare maiden for him, tossing up the googly to complete the over
nudged off the legs
goes down to try and sweep, misses the ball and takes it on the thigh - maybe a little slower from Moeen
on the stumps, turned to leg
comes forward and drives to the man in the covers
flighted, worked across the line, in front of midwicket and they pinch one
angled in with the arm, blocked back to the bowler
on the stumps, tucked towards midwicket
tossed up, goes for the slog-sweep and miscues it along the ground towards long-on
tossed up, nice and juicy outside off, Sarfraz takes a big bit, getting his front foot out and clubbing past deep extra cover
tip and run, towards mid-on, the ball is underarmed at the stumps but missed and Sarfraz had made good ground
pushed through slightly wide, Taylor makes a diving stop at backward point
width to cut again but Taylor pounces on it in almost identical fashion
tossed up on the stumps and pushed towards mid-on
closes the face, gets a leading edge back towards the bowler
outside off, cut to backward point
gets down low and sweeps one more through backward square leg
can't get this one away
tossed up on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler - tight few overs from England, nine runs off the last four
starts with a wide down the leg side
goes across and nudges a length ball to leg
on the hips, tucked away through backward square
Willey continues to bowl a leg-stump line, clipped away for one more
on the legs, nudged square to the man in the deep
pushed across the batsman, room to free the arms and slap one behind point
a change of pace deceives Hafeez, he tries to pull and it bops him in the gut
gets down and sweeps one more through backward square leg
pushed back to the bowler
tossed up on the stumps, can't get the ball past midwicket
tossed up outside off, driven firmly but straight to the man set back in the covers
popped back towards the bowler again
angled in and turned around the corner for a single to finish the over
length ball around the line of off, pushed in front of square

low full toss from Willey, the cat-like Sarfraz is low in the crease and into the sweep early, picks out backward square but runs anyway, a direct hit would have been close... Think there was a vain lbw appeal, too, but must have been glove/bat on it first
length  ball, dabbed into the covers
top-edged out towards deep square leg... and taken! Hafeez's slow wind down comes to its conclusion with a tame flick into the deep, miscued it high to the fielder
back of a length, tucked away through square
goes across his stumps and flicks his first ball away for a run
punched back past the bowler to long-on
worked into the leg side

comes charging down the pitch, slogs to leg - and picks out the fielder in the deep! Sarfraz has a brain fart and hands his wicket to Moeen! He was going so well but tried to force it, just after losing his partner
pushed through flat on off stump, drops back and cut
flighted, spinning in to hit the inside edge as Malik props forward
length ball, tapped square from the crease
pitched up outside off and pushed through the covers into the deep
back of a length on leg stump, misses with a flick
pushed into the covers coming forwards
Willey joining the dots here, as Malik punches a fullish ball to extra cover
short ball on the stumps, pulled flat through square leg
full around off stump, slower delivery and Rizwan pats it to cover
pushed to the right of the bowler for one

another run-out, Rizwan wandering down the pitch! Either he didn't call or Malik didn't hear it because he wasn't moving, Rizwan realised far too late and Roy was able to scoop the ball up at midwicket, underarm to Buttler, who completed the dismissal
spinning down the leg side, gets a leading edge
turned into the leg side
angled in with the arm, pushed back
Moeen darts the ball on the stumps, Iftikhar blocks - just one off the over, to go with the run-out
stays in the crease and blocks
short of a length, drops back and nudged through square
dabbed into a gap, Iftikhar is off the mark
slanted across the right-hander from over the wicket, glided to third man
goes full around the line of off, driven with a statesmanlike air through mid-off
slower ball from Willey, hits the toe of the bat as he props forward
on the stumps, flicked into the leg side
pushed through on off stump, blocked back to the bowler
length ball on off, closes the face and turns it to midwicket
slower, floated up outside off, leans out and defends
spinning in off a length, goes back and whips it away to deep midwicket for one
bit of dip, gripping to spin in on off, Iftikhar shows it a straight bat
full and straight, driven to mid-n

there's an appeal for lbw by Woakes as this nips back, an off-cutter, and is deflected to third man. Pad first? Hard to tell. Seems to be flap of the front pad. No review used. Going over in any event
clipped to midwicket
and another! Falling in a heap here. Another short-ball wicket for Woakes as Iftikhar goes to pull, gets elevation but not the distance and picks out deep square-leg.
tight to off stump, dabbed through backward point
full at straight, driven to mid-off
steps back to leg and drives out to deep cover
appeal for lbw, full around leg stump, Anwar probs forward, probably not straightening enough...might have pitched outside leg, too
wide outside off, left alone
pushed square into the off side and a rare fumble in the field from England by Woakes coming across from point

another appeal for lbw and this time England use their review. A googly from Rashid, nice spin to beat the inside edge. Has it done too much? Unless there's an edge. Well, hitting in line with off stump is umpire's call and it's also going over
full and pushed down the ground
full at the stumps, played back to Woakes in his followthrough
short ball, over off stump, Anwar ducks
full outside off, might have been another cutter, patted to the off side
flicked into the leg side
short delivery dug in, rises fairly gently off the surface, worked around the corner behind square
push-and-run towards mid-on, it was a bit of a scamper but safe enough
driven into the covers
driven away square through point, but Moeen is quickly around at deep cover
flicks a full delivery to midwicket

was that a missed stumping?? Yes, it was. Buttler can't glove it cleanly as Anwar plays over the top of a full delivery. Won't help Buttler's confidence. Anwar was out of his crease for quite some time.
beaten by one which spins, nice bowling
driven down the ground
full outside off, played to backward point
shorter delivery, again he can't beat backward point as he opens the face

this has gone miles in the air and is safely taken! Another bit of pretty brainless cricket from Pakistan as Anwar tries to launch this back towards Dubai, it's a back-of-a-length ball and it gets way underneath it. Moeen does well to settle under a steepler
full at the stumps, tries to work to the on side but gets it towards mid-off instead
that's a pretty ugly heave into the leg side, swinging across the line of a full delivery
full and straight, blocked to the off side
angled down to third man
a length delivery, runs it off the edge to third man
and another down to third man...it's about all Pakistan can do for the next five or six overs
short outside off, leaves it alone
fuller, comes forward and pushes to backward point, Roy very quickly in
a short-of-a-length cutter which is prodded into the off side
angled down to third man

another run out! Waqar not impressed in the dressing room. It was just nudged into midwicket, Malik came charging up the pitch, it's a swift pick-up by Jordan and a direct hit on the turn. Excellent work, but what has happened to Pakistan?
flicked off the pads to long leg
nearly run-out No. 4! He digs out a yorker towards mid-on, Wahab charges out of his crease and has to dive to get back in
slower ball outside off which he nearly spoons to cover
tapped to the off side
low full toss which is squirted down to third man
worked from offstump to midwicket
full outside off, heaved down the ground to long on
driven through the off side
low full toss, aiming for the yorker, can only get swung to long on
full on the pads, clipped to deep midwicket
excellent yorker, dug out back to the bowler
gets beaten by another slower one outside off as he tries to cut
driven square through the off side
dropped into the off side, a tight single...could have been close with a direct hit. Probably out with a hit!

a controlled edge down to third man, he comes back for a dicey second and has to dive to make his crease...the ball bounce awkwardly at Buttler who couldn't gather it. Might have had time to break the stumps
driven to deep cover
cut firmly out to deep point
swings a low full toss in the air over square leg, deep midwicket gets around, they wanted a second for a moment but settled at one
full outside off, he drives over the top of it
deflected down to third man
a boundary! And it's the full lot. Terrific shot on debut, gets good leverage on a full ball, stays in the crease, swings through the line over long-on
misses out on a low full toss this time, clipped to midwicket
dabbed to backward point
another cutter, beats him on the inside edge as he aims to the leg side...actually, a back-of-the-hand slower ball
on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket
good bit of invention now from Gohar, steps across his crease and scoops a full toss behind square...he doesn't lack for confidence
slices this in the air, down the ground, but it lands short of long off
another slower one outside off, he misses his dab
lovely strike and, I think, superb fielding...lofted straight down the ground over mid-off, but it doesn't skip across the outfield and gets flicked back
swing and a miss to a full ball outside off
gone this time, swinging to leg against a back-of-a-length delivery and gets a top edge through to Buttler. Been a short-ball day for Woakes
full outside off, driven to cover
yorker, dug out to the off side
full and straight, manages to keep it out with a nudge to mid-on
full and straight, aims to swing down the ground, slices as the bat turns and lobs towards mid-off but he declines the single
he's connected this time! Almost a slog-sweep, goes down on one knee and picks it from outside off with a mighty swing over deep midwicket
dropped! A blemish from England. He heaves this into the leg side, picks out deep square where Root shells one that he would normally swallow
that came out wrong, a loopy full toss slower ball which Irfan lets through to the keeper then questions if it should have been a no-ball. Waist height to Irfan is a beaming to other players
full outside off, jabbed to point...crowd cheering the blocks from Irfan
a straight, low full toss which is carefully pushed to cover so he survives the over
a yorker which is driven firmly to cover who is on the edge of the circle
top edge, but falls into space! And in the end it's a dot ball. Back of a length, heaves to the leg side, takes a top edge and doesn't carry to long on
cracked straight down the ground this time and the run is declined again
this time he gets it! Short of a length, Wahab keeps swinging hard and he muscles it over deep midwicket to bring up Pakistan's 200
full on the pads, deflects into the leg side, straight back to the bowler so can't get the single
works a low full toss into the vacant midwicket area and trots the single
another fantastic strike! Not the best delivery from Woakes, a driveable length outside off, and it gets absolutely hammered, flat over long-off
he's given lbw but reviews straight away. Hit it? Yes, massive inside edge into the back pad so this will be overturned

he's given lbw again! And he reviews again. Wasn't an instant review this time. This one might be missing leg. Hit the back foot full, but very leg-side. Missing leg stump. He survives again. What scenes
now he tries to scoop, gets across outside off and flicks it behind square on the leg side
cleaned up! Full, straight, Irfan swung and Woakes hit off stump...he finishes with four wickets, so eight in his last two innings

inn2.comm: full and a touch wide and Roy gets out to lash it through the covers, positive intent from the off
draws his length back a touch, this zips through as Roy plays no stroke
gets forward, check-drives this time, into a gap in the covers and gets a couple more
pushes from the crease, inside-edged through backward square
slightly back of a length, in the channel and Hales lets it go
bit of width, Hales toe-ends a cut in the air down towards third man, could have gone awry but picks up a single to get off the mark
starts slightly short, tapped into the covers
slides on to the pads, Hales clips it past the diving short fine leg and gets a boundary to his name
defends coming forwards around off stump
length ball, Hales shows it a straight bat
angled in and worked off the body short into the leg side
good length on off stump, Hales shows it a straight bat in defence once again
slower ball from Irfan, poked off the hips towards square

extra lift from a length and Roy spoons it to cover! The giant picks up his first victim, he punches the air in delight... Roy was pushing out in front of him, closing the face slightly and a thick leading edge flew towards the edge of the ring
bowling round the wicket, pitched up and defended coming forwards
length ball slightly wide of the stumps, left alone
pushed into the covers coming across
short outside off, 86mph and steered away with a horizontal bat down to third man
slightly short of a length and defended into the off side
pitched up and punched towards mid-on, Root takes on the fielder and although he has to detour around Anwar he gets in okay
goes back and runs one to third man
pitched up, Root skips out and opens the face, steers it past backward point
full and straight, clipped off the toes through square leg
dropped short by Anwar and Root thwocks a pull away to the square-leg boundary with control to spare
leading edge, back to the bowler, he collapses like a felled oak... and drops it! He actually did well to fall right into its path, stuck out a big left paw and then grassed it, off the wrist
back and across and runs the ball to third man
jumps back and lets this one go

slammed in short, a snorter at 88mph and Root is fending blindly in front of his face, loops off the glove behind square - no catcher in. Actually, his bottom hand was off the bat when it hit the glove
short of a length, steered towards backward point
another fiery bumper from Irfan, the batsman collapses underneath
pushed through outside off, goes back and sends a cut towards point
pitched up and punched into a gap in the covers coming forwards
angled in with the arm from round the wicket, clipped off the legs behind square
drops a little short, Root pulls in the air over midwicket, shouts of "catch!" but it was well in front of the man in the deep and they get back for two

Root slogs a full toss straight to deep square leg! Wicket in his first over for Gohar, he'll bowl better balls for less reward in his international career, for sure, but they don't add descriptions in the scorebook. Root just shovelled it straight to Iftikhar a few yards in, took a good catch above his head
flat on the stumps, clipped past the dive of midwicket for a single
gets across and defends a length ball
short and down the leg side
oof, Morgan is hit on the shoulder trying to pull a bouncer, he looks in a bit of discomfort initially but seems okay... Though the shot early, deflected off the upper arm into the helmet
goes round the wicket, full on the legs, Morgan gets a scrape of bat on it
bangs in the short ball, at the batsman, who ducks sharpish
ooh, that's a beauty, a cutter from Irfan that beats the bat by a distance, bobbles low through to the keeper
nips one past the outside edge again! Gets some extravagant movement by rolling his fingers over it, superb stuff
over the wicket, pushed back down the track

tossed up and driven hard, in the air, straight back at the bowler... who doesn't lay a hand on it, though he does take a blow on the arm, the ball deflecting away through mid-on. A tough, tough chance, Gohar couldn't react in time
tossed up and worked through the leg side for a single
sliding on with the arm, Hales flicks it behind square on the leg side
leans into a forward defensive
short outside off, Hales reaches for a cut and was perilously close to nicking off
unplayable! Short and rising towards the shoulder, moved late too, just past the gloves
drops back and runs a single to third man
shortish, lets this one through
bangs it in short and Morgan flinches out of the way
good length, 86mph around off stump, defended into the covers - excellent over from Irfan
pushed into a gap for one
flighted outside off, leans out and defends
angled in, played with the spin wide of mid-on
length outside off, Hales chops it into the covers
plants the front foot and plants him into the stands! The slog-sweep from Hales, utilising his long reach, absolutely hammered over the rope
quicker ball from Gohar, nearly catches Hales unawares, jams the bat down in time
presses forward and defends solidly around off
drops short and Morgan dismissively pulls it flat through backward square for four, looked comfortable with that
length outside off, comes forward and plays through the covers
slightly short, up towards 90mph, Hales reaches outside off and bottom-edges through to the keeper on the bounce
slower ball from Wahab, a cutter that Hales can only push back down the track
targeting the stumps, 87mph and played late, chopped into the ground towards backward point
tossed up, pushed back to the bowler
makes room to try and cut, gets an inside edge towards midwicket
pushed through flat on off stump, punched into the covers
good length, chopped towards cover from the crease
pushed through flat outside off, drops back and sends the ball to point - another dot
gets on to the front foot and drives, gets it past mid-off and they trot a single. Decent start from Iftikhar, though

pushed into the leg side, they steal a single... but the throw to the non-striker's end is a direct hit, with Morgan having to swerve round the bowler. It looked close but he was comfortably home in the end
slightly short, outside off, Hales reaches out and squirts one to third man
good length around the line of off, Morgan shows it a straight bat
slower ball from Wahab, just 66mph and Morgan is through the shot early, plays it on the full and in the air but lands short of mid-off
short and heading down the leg side, Morgan helps it on its way down to fine leg with a swat of the bat
shortish, 87mph outside off, runs one more to third man
goes back and across and pushes into a gap
stays round the wicket, tossed up on the pads, deflects behind square
angled in flat on the stumps, Morgan defends back down the track
slightly short, punched down the ground to long-off
darted on the stumps and Hales crunches a sweep into the gap between deep midwicket and fine leg, that's four
tossed up a little more, dabbed towards square leg
Morgan gets across to defend a 88mph delivery without fuss
good length, moves into line and defends again
slower ball, waits for it and clips one to deep square leg
short at the body, 88mph and jabbed away square on the leg side
full and wide of the off stump, Hales dabs it down to third man
length around the line of off, Morgan bows his head over it in defence
floated up and clipped through midwicket to the man in the deep
pushed through outside off, turning away fractionally as Morgan slaps it through backward point
over the wicket, length ball, played with the turn to square leg
flighted, flicked off the toes behind square
oh, well bowled, beats everything! Morgan tried to drive through the off side, the ball pitched on middle and off, spun past the bat, past the timber and into the gloves
skidding on this time, clips the inside edge and runs behind square on the leg side
full outside off, guides this away behind point
straight delivery, just back of a length, defended to midwicket
a bouncer over leg stump, Hales ducks, and it's too leg side (or short) for the umpire
driven into the ground and it bounces to backward point
tucks this one off his hip into square leg
short outside off, another slower ball, not much pace to work with and it plops (I'm sure that's a term in the MCC coaching manual) through the off side
trying to guide this down to third man, angled across him, and the ball beats the top edge
slides in from round the wicket, cut into the off side
forward with bat and pad together
brings out the reverse sweep, or club, as though it is an everyday shot - which for him it is - and swats it away from wide outside off through third man
fuller, driven to cover
edged! But doesn't carry to slip. Nice turn as Morgan comes forward, but it dies off the outside edge

a mighty appeal for a catch down the leg side! Malik and Sarfraz are convinced Hales has touched this. Umpire Raza says not out and they review. Clipped the thigh pad? Looks a good decision. And, yep, it stays onfield
and he's met by a powerful reverse sweep from Morgan, a slightly fuller delivery than the one he struck last time, gets right over the top and it whistles along the ground
flicked from outside off to midwicket
appeal for lbw but that's struck him well outside the line, Morgan trying to flick it to the leg side
another huge shout! This has more going for it. Morgan back in his crease, sharp spin to take the pad but may have been going down leg. The review is gone, remember
more very sharp spin, this one goes down the leg side and is called wide
grip and spin, Morgan takes his bottom hand off the bat...worth a short leg? Pakistan need wickets
full outside off, he thrusts his bat in front of the pad this time as he blocks...interesting over
they are screaming for everything at the moment, Hales taken on the pad from round the wicket as he plays back, it gripped again, and deflects through fine leg...going down
plays back again, flicked through midwicket
full on middle and leg, tapped to the on side
defended to cover
full at off stump, small stride forward, block (leg slip has become slip for Morgan)
shoves this one down the leg side, no contact with anything
full at the stumps, defended square into the off side
full and straight, pushed to the covers
swept off the stumps and Irfan dives (or collapses) over it at short fine-leg
done him! It was on the cards. Lovely bowling. Floated up full, Hales leans forward and prods in front of his pads, the outside edge carries low to slip
full at off stump, driven to cover
pushed up very full, blocked back down the pitch...plenty of noise in the field and the stands
a beauty! Was that an edge? It's gone to third man. Big spin and turn. Defeats Taylor's edge as he prods forward, the keeper and slip
round the wicket, full at off stump, defended
touch shorter, Morgan rocks back and drives through the covers
round the wicket, swept to deep square leg
gets this through the infield, a hint of width outside off, Morgan cuts through point but there's a boot on it near the boundary
and another! Lovely delivery, but Morgan has missed it by a long way. Playing back, it pitched on middle, turned sharply and struck off stump. Morgan comprehensively defeated
plays back, deflects off the pad wide of leg slip
forward and defended
another edge! Taylor also going back, more sharp spin - it goes square - takes the edge but Taylor's hands are soft it beats slip having not carried
you can feel the pressure, now he tries to sweep and doesn't make contact
makes use of a low full toss outside leg stump, gets over the top and sweeps it wide of short fine-leg...Malik tries to get there, but slips on the boundary edge. Looks in a bit of pain
touch short, driven out to the cover sweeper
a play and a miss from Buttler, it was short and he went back to cut but there was extra bounce to beat the top edge
round the wicket, full outside off, driven down the ground
missed stumping, Buttler came down the pitch, yorked himself, played over the top of the delivery, Sarfraz couldn't make the take. Buttler was a long way down
goes back and works a straight delivery with the spin to the leg side
short, spins down the leg side, a rare poor delivery
sweeps this very hard off the stumps, sweetly connected, but almost straight to deep square
full and a touch wide, Buttler comes forward and drives wide of the cover sweeper
gets over the ball and drives to long on
well, that takes some guts, reverse sweeps and places it very well wide of backward point
terrific response from Gohar, floated up at off stump, spins past Buttler's edge as he lunges forward
that's even better! Unplayable. Pitched around middle and leg, rips past the outside edge and off stump. Jeepers.
this is fantastic cricket, Buttler brings out the reverse sweep again, not quite as clean as the previous one but gets it finer and beats short third man
adjusts his line, drifts full onto leg stump, clipped through midwicket and placed well enough for a second
drags this a little short, driven to deep cover
round the wicket, full outside off, eased down the ground to long on
uses his feet then whips to midwicket
down the pitch again, flicks this through the vacant short fine-leg area...the running will be quick with this pair
back into the crease again, plays with the spin behind square on the leg side
down the pitch, not quite to the ball, has to lunge at it as he defends
gets down and plays a neat paddle-sweep from outside leg
dragged down short outside off, Taylor pulls hard through midwicket
short and wide, a fairly horrid ball, and a fairly horrid shot as Taylor swipes and misses
full at the stumps, driven back to the bowler
whipped from full outside off with the bottom hand towards mid-on
pushed way down the leg side
think that was the googly, not sure Buttler picked it, went for the reverse sweep and gets a bottom edge to short third man
beats him again, a quick ball outside off which also turns, defeats Taylor's cut and he's angry with himself
staying round the wicket, opens the face and places to deep point
tries to work this into space on the leg side but finds midwicket
a bottom-handed flick through midwicket, the ball was full outside off, good placement wide of the deep sweeper
that's a big blow! Enough of the tippy-tappy for Taylor, he comes down the pitch then goes with the spin high over deep midwicket with a pick-up shot
now he works a flatter ball off the pads wide of leg side
full, blocked
very full, dug out through the covers to the sweeper
ooh, that's a big full toss, but only costs a single as Taylor swats to deep midwicket
pitches this one, full and straight, flicked through midwicket to bring up a very brisk 50-runs stand
sharp spin! Rips away from the outside edge, but think Taylor pulled his bat inside the line this time
shorter, cut to backward point
short and wide, but Taylor cuts straight to cover
full at middle and off, forward and defended to cover
defended to the bowler
back of a length on off stump, neatly driven out to deep cover
on his toes, pinged to mid-off
tries to force this through the off side but he's cramped for room
full at the stumps, Taylor shuffling across the crease and defends
round the wicket, a slower short ball, defeats Buttler as he goes for a square swat
nearly finds third man! Short of a length outside off, Buttler cuts and slices it just in front of the fielder...one bounce
short outside off, Taylor gets over the top and plays to deep point
opens the face and places this calmly through point to the sweeper
short, angled into the body, Taylor rolls his wrists on the pull down to long leg
full at off stump, 76mph, defended to cover
tries to force through the off side, gets a thick inside edge which isn't a million miles from the stumps
short ball, 83mph, Taylor responds with a rasping pull which skims, one bounce, to fine leg
full outside off, 89mph, driven to the cover sweeper
comes forward, nearly punches this in the air to cover but just stops himself from going too hard
back of a length, smartly dropped into the off side and they steal a single that probably shouldn't have been on offer
short, on leg stump, pulled to deep square
full at the stumps, driven firmly at cover
juicy full toss which is swung through the leg side but only a single to deep midwicket
appeal for lbw, Taylor flicking across the line of a full ball, heading leg side and may have hit it as well
another shout for lbw, Taylor on the sweep, pitched outside leg by looks of it
this one spins, defends square to the off side
goes back, takes the pad to the leg side
short of a length outside off, drops back and dabs to third man
drops short again, at the body, Taylor swivels quickly to pull
fullish, mid-80s mph in the channel, Buttler presses out and steers through cover
shouts of "catch!" as Taylor mistimes an aerial drive, his bottom hand coming off the bat... but it clears mid-ff and bounces away to the rope, brings the requirement under 50 now
short and pulled hard - four more! Wahab dived at deep backward square but could only help the ball on to the boundary
length delivery, Taylor comes forward to block
tossed up, Buttler get out and punches through a gap
angled in and turned away through the leg side
drops back, waits for the ball to turn away from him, stabs through point
tossed up and patted away into the off side
serves up a full toss and Taylor bunts it low past mid-on, it has the legs to outrun long-off for another boundary
looped up on off stump, leans into a forward defensive
pushed through and steered square off the back foot
full toss, Taylor gives it the big 'un and charges out to slap it through mid-off... in fact, he lands it right on the rope to bring up his fifty with a six!
round the wicket, tossed up on the stumps, dabbed into the leg side
pushed across the right-hander, runs it to backward point
flighted, on leg stump, goes down low to sweep behind square
on leg stump, tapped into a gap at square leg
slightly short, Buttler chops hard into the the covers but a diving stop prevents any runs
pushed back down the track
drops back and gets his cut through the infield this time
drops back on off stump but doesn't quite connect properly

drifting towards leg stump, gets down low to sweep, towards deep backward square... who then underarms a throw towards a team-mate who wasn't looking and Taylor briefly thinks about coming back for two
on off stump, reverse swept through backward point for a couple more

Taylor sweeps, top-edges towards deep square leg... who misses it completely! Gohar is signalling he couldn't see it in the lights as he ran in, the ball landed near his foot and bounced away for four
outside leg and Taylor gets some glove on a sweep to loop it up and over leg slip this time
tossed up on the stumps and swept fine for one more
Taylor skips out and nurdles into the leg side
short and glanced off the hips from back in the crease - they scurry two more and that's the 100 stand between these two, looking like a match-winner
on the stumps, flicked leg side for one more
round the wicket, nudged through square leg
tossed up and blocked back on the leg side
flat offbreak down leg, flicked away to deep backward square
turned to leg from the crease
leg-stump line, hits the pads and rolls away
flighted, Buttler waits on it and taps back down the track, no longer in any hurry
length on the stumps and flicked behind square
drops short, sits up nicely to be pulled through midwicket for one
shortish, over the top of off, Taylor closes the face and nudges square to the leg side
back of a length outside off, Buttler dabs it down to third man - 200 up for England, they're getting there without breaking sweat now
shortish, 78mph outside off, Taylor glides another single to third man
gets across and pushes gently into the off side
length outside leg stump, tapped away
goes down on one knee very early, waits for the ball to come on and flicks a paddle shot over his shoulder for a couple
over the wicket, pushed through and blocked
flat on the stumps, defended again
shuffles forward, clips back to the bowler's right... a misfield gives Taylor one more

there it is, crashed over deep midwicket for the winning hit! Buttler saunters out and clubs the ball well beyond the rope to finish unbeaten on 49, as England win by six wickets to go 2-1 up in the series
